{"TopicId":196904,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"Life on Venus?","CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-14T15:25:44Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-14T15:25:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.reuters.com/article/us-space-exploration-venus/potential-sign-of-alien-life-detected-on-inhospitable-venus-idUSKBN2652GO\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.reuters.com/article/us-space-exploration-venus/potential-sign-of-alien-life-detected-on-inhospitable-venus-idUSKBN2652GO\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, now there\u0027s a really good reason to send a floating mission to the clouds there.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-14T15:29:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSomeone beat me to it Dangit!\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\nReally the only way to confirm is via spacecraft. May make one of the four NASA probes currently in review chosen.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Commodore_32","CreatedById":200414,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-14T15:31:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223854142\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022196904\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221600097370\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022196529\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022The Doodling Astronaut\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, The Doodling Astronaut said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMay make one of the four NASA probes currently in review chosen.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh I would love to see it!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-14T15:33:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.nasa.gov/press-release/nasa-selects-four-possible-missions-to-study-the-secrets-of-the-solar-system\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.nasa.gov/press-release/nasa-selects-four-possible-missions-to-study-the-secrets-of-the-solar-system\u003C/a\u003E\u0027\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis discovery may just make DAVINCHI\u002B chosen. The team might be very excited to be the team to discover aliens!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKinda crazy to think... that we once explored Venus heavily and said there must be no life there... I was taught there was no way at all Venus would have life in school.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdit:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.hou.usra.edu/meetings/lpsc2020/pdf/2599.pdf\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.hou.usra.edu/meetings/lpsc2020/pdf/2599.pdf\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-09-14T15:47:46Z\u0022 title=\u002209/14/2020 03:47  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 14, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Guest\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-14T15:50:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed242972269\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/Dr_ThomasZ/status/1305526347595358208\u0022 style=\u0022height:708px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-14T15:54:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo the Venusians and the Martians distribute, who produces methane and who produces phosphine?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr somebody wants a Venus research funding?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-14T15:57:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223854159\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022196904\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221600098885\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo the Venusians and the Martians distribute, who produces methane and who produces phosphine?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr somebody wants a Venus research funding?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPhosphine tho in the amounts they are seeing isn\u0027t something you see without bacteria\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMethane on the other hand could be produced by bacteria on Mars but could also be a geological event happening\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-14T16:01:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223854162\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022196904\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221600099065\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022196529\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022The Doodling Astronaut\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, The Doodling Astronaut said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPhosphine tho in the amounts they are seeing isn\u0027t something you see without bacteria\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMethane on the other hand could be produced by bacteria on Mars but could also be a geological event happening\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut where is the Venusian bacterial methane then?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KSK","CreatedById":61025,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-14T16:05:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBah - might have known I\u0027d be ninjaed. Just finished listening to the press conference - really interesting stuff.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey\u0027re being understandably cagey about claiming detection of life - not least because the amount of sulphuric acid in Venus\u0027 atmosphere makes it very unlikely that anything resembling terrestrial organisms could survive. On the other hand, they\u0027ve eliminated all the non-biological routes to producing phosphine - their models are falling short there by several orders of magnitude.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, as somebody pointed out on Twitter (I forget who, sorry), we\u0027ve got novel chemistry, unexplained spectroscopy or possible life happening here, all of which are pretty interesting!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-09-14T16:06:19Z\u0022 title=\u002209/14/2020 04:06  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 14, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by KSK\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-14T16:09:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223854167\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022196904\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221600099548\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002261025\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022KSK\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 minutes ago, KSK said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOn the other hand, they\u0027ve eliminated all the non-biological routes to producing phosphine - their models are falling short there by several orders of magnitude.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, either a life lives, or the models are wrong. I vote for the former!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nP.S.\u003Cbr\u003E\nIs that NASA poll about the future researches still active?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-09-14T16:12:25Z\u0022 title=\u002209/14/2020 04:12  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 14, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by kerbiloid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KSK","CreatedById":61025,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-14T16:11:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223854171\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022196904\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221600099766\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, either a life lives, or the models are wrong. I vote for the former!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOK, I should probably correct myself. They\u0027ve eliminated all the non-biological routes using chemistry that they\u0027re aware of. \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0 That\u0027s not ruling out unknown chemistry but it\u0027s hard to say much about that, it being unknown and all.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-14T16:12:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHonestly there have been too many false claims in the past where I don\u0027t want to get too excited\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\nI like how all the non science people hearing this think it\u0027s some kind of animal\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:rolleyes:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_rolleyes.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:rolleyes:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s bacteria if it is, or some kind of extremophile\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dr. Kerbal","CreatedById":207217,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-14T16:25:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nVenus may have life. We have found life on earth in crazy places; volcanoes, nuclear reactor, anartica, and more!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-09-14T16:26:07Z\u0022 title=\u002209/14/2020 04:26  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 14, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Dr. Kerbal\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003Em\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sevenperforce","CreatedById":157695,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-14T16:59:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe cool thing, I think,\u00A0is that this is the most likely way of finding life on another planet. We would see novel chemistry first.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"coyotesfrontier","CreatedById":181596,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-14T17:05:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBizarrely, the announcement seemed to have been predicted in a 4chan thread last Friday. I can\u0027t post the thread here as 4chan is very much a NSFW site, but I can DM anyone who wants to see it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00223iQcBto.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002223.40\u0022 height=\u0022280\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/3iQcBto.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sevenperforce","CreatedById":157695,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-14T17:10:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223854210\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022196904\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221600103123\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022181596\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022coyotesfrontier\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, coyotesfrontier said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBizarrely, the announcement seemed to have been predicted in a 4chan thread last Friday. I can\u0027t post the thread here as 4chan is very much a NSFW site, but I can DM anyone who wants to see it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/3iQcBto.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u00223iQcBto.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002223.40\u0022 height=\u0022280\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/3iQcBto.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt was leaked.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"coyotesfrontier","CreatedById":181596,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-14T17:11:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223854214\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022196904\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221600103409\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022157695\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sevenperforce\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, sevenperforce said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt was leaked.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, that\u0027s it. Probably shouldn\u0027t have posted it, I should have thought about it more.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-09-14T17:12:43Z\u0022 title=\u002209/14/2020 05:12  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 14, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by coyotesfrontier\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-14T17:29:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m being reminded of a certain thread where I made some bold claims about life in extreme conditions, and quite a few people reacted with disbelief. \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0I can\u0027t say that I expected that, but I can say that given what we know, the idea is plausible. That said, if this is true, then we\u0027re in for some really weird stuff. Extremophiles on Earth are bizarre enough, but Venus?\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTBH, given those results, whatever\u0027s causing them would be pretty weird whether it\u0027s really life or not. Oh, well, it\u0027s an exciting time to be in biophysics. \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0I\u0027m currently specializing towards things that happen in humans, but if they really find extraplanetary life I think I\u0027ll switch. \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"magnemoe","CreatedById":57801,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-14T19:17:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223854209\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022196904\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221600102744\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022157695\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sevenperforce\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, sevenperforce said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe cool thing, I think,\u00A0is that this is the most likely way of finding life on another planet. We would see novel chemistry first.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat has been true for some time as in exo planets.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nHelium was first identified on the sun \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nNow its that star with trans uranium elements\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.newscientist.com/article/2125615-oddball-star-could-be-home-to-long-sought-superheavy-elements/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.newscientist.com/article/2125615-oddball-star-could-be-home-to-long-sought-superheavy-elements/\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0is much weirder \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sevenperforce","CreatedById":157695,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-14T19:23:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223854280\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022196904\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221600111038\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257801\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022magnemoe\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 minutes ago, magnemoe said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat has been true for some time as in exo planets.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nHelium was first identified on the sun \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nNow its that star with trans uranium elements\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.newscientist.com/article/2125615-oddball-star-could-be-home-to-long-sought-superheavy-elements/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.newscientist.com/article/2125615-oddball-star-could-be-home-to-long-sought-superheavy-elements/\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0is much weirder \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI remember one of my first actual upper-level physics lab projects was rediscovering the absorption lines in the stellar spectrum.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-14T19:38:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/GWj85r02Oiw?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Image\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022125.00\u0022 width=\u00221080\u0022 src=\u0022https://pbs.twimg.com/media/Eh44lKKWsAAsmQv?format=jpg\u0026amp;name=large\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"coyotesfrontier","CreatedById":181596,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-14T19:48:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan anyone here estimate the probability that this turns out to be correct, and there actually is life on Venus?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-14T19:49:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Eh5jMmqWkAAkhJP?format=png\u0026amp;name=900x900\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022123.52\u0022 height=\u0022688\u0022 width=\u0022557\u0022 src=\u0022https://pbs.twimg.com/media/Eh5jMmqWkAAkhJP?format=png\u0026amp;name=900x900\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sevenperforce","CreatedById":157695,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-14T20:01:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223854300\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022196904\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221600112916\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022181596\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022coyotesfrontier\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 minutes ago, coyotesfrontier said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan anyone here estimate the probability that this turns out to be correct, and there actually is life on Venus?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, I can make the estimate. It\u0027s 50-50.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nError bars on that estimate are rather large, though.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-14T20:03:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe know phosphine can be naturally produced in high temperatures, this happens on Jupiter, for instance.\u00A0What got people so excited is that\u00A0Venus is hot, but not \u003Cem\u003Ethat\u003C/em\u003E hot. Either there\u0027s some place in there where there\u0027s a 500K\u002B hotspot, or some other process is at work here. This could be geochemistry, but one thing life does is produce molecules that are typically difficult to make otherwise.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis actually got me thinking. We know terrestrial life can make phosphine, and that there are species that\u00A0could survive in the atmosphere of Venus. Were the Venera probes decontaminated? I\u0027m not sure if Soviets had an equivalent to Planetary Protection Officer at the time, and even if they did, they knew Venus was a hellhole back then, and extremophiles were poorly researched at the time. I wonder, what are the chances that one of those hitched a ride in one of the parachute containers, or on a balloon probe, and, having found a perfect environment, spread far enough for its metabolites to show up? It\u0027s a rather disturbing thought.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}